author: @R0bobb1e

text:
It's true, I was specifically told that "you'll know they're working if you don't feel anything. So don't quit taking them just because you don't think they're working." 
Fast forward 2 hours: I feel as though the house could be burning down around me and I literally wouldn't move because I wouldn't give a fuck. Also I felt like my blood was boiling, and like hydrogen peroxide was being dumped on my brain (that bubbling sensation.) Turns out I didn't need them because I wasn't depressed- I just had the occasional anxiety attack and sometimes antidepressants help with that, apparently. Except the reason I was feeling those terrible side effects is because I was bordering on Serotonin poisoning. So I guess something about being in your early 20's, a new mother with the occassional crippling anxiety attack (and I'm sure living in Portland didn't help) my doctor make the assumption that I MUST be medically depressed. So just remember, the problem with being "at the top" of good mental and physical health is that you can only go down from there!
